Karnataka has many natural and historical attractions that make it a top tourist destination. Its beaches, Western Ghat mountain ranges, forests, rivers, waterfalls, and wildlife sanctuaries provide natural beauty. Historically, various ruling dynasties have left behind forts, temples, mosques and other architectural marvels across the state. Popular destinations include Jog Falls, Shivasamudra Falls, Gokak Falls, wildlife parks, religious sites of multiple faiths, and the cultural cities of Bijapur and Gulbarga with their historic mosques, mausoleums and shrines.
